The paper deals with denoising methods, which are often studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The use of ensemble methods and machine learning techniques suggests a possible fit with the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also proposes a stopping criterion for greedy pursuit algorithms, which is related to numerical analysis and optimization, and could be relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on MEG signals, which are related to neuroscience and could be relevant to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
